      <h1>FPC Roller Adhesive Cleaner Selection Guide: Key Criteria for Manufacturing Decision Makers</h1>
      <p class="blog-lead">
        Selecting a roller adhesive cleaning machine for flexible printed circuit manufacturing is not a price decision — it is a process compatibility decision. FPC substrates are thin, electrostatically sensitive, and intolerant of surface contamination at scales that general-purpose cleaning equipment cannot reliably address. A cleaner that leaves adhesive residue on copper foil, generates static discharge during transport, or cannot maintain stable tension through a reel-to-reel process will produce yield losses that far exceed any procurement cost saving. This guide addresses the selection criteria that matter for FPC decision makers: <strong>cleaning precision, substrate compatibility, static elimination integration, process-stage fit, and long-term operational cost</strong>.
      </p>

